parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Evaporator and Emission Control System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel evaporator and emission control system can cause the vehicle to stall, hesitate, and have problems starting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: and has problems starting shortly after filling up the gas tank
especially when the fuel level is low; the vehicle hesitates
and when coming to a full stop; the vehicle hesitates and misfires during acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the horn to malfunction, leading to a distraction while driving, and can also cause other systems to malfunction, such as the dash radio, phone, and cruise control.
symptoms: The horn goes off automatically when the car is started; the dash radio and phone are not working properly; the cruise control is not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The cruise control accelerates or decelerates unexpectedly; the vehicle lurches or surges while in cruise control; the engine throttles up and accelerates when the brake is applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery or electrical system can cause the vehicle to require frequent jump-starting, leading to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle requires frequent jump-starting; the dealer is unable to diagnose the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbocharger failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to difficulty accelerating, especially on hills and in traffic, which can increase the risk of accidents.
Engine performance issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to difficulty accelerating, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: vehicle doesn't speed up past 75 mph
gears change and jerk when trying to accelerate

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air induction system failure can cause the engine and transmission system to malfunction, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine and transmission system not performing as expected
issue detected in the air induction system

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected shattering of the sunroof can cause a loud noise, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries from shattered glass.
symptoms: Abnormal sound coming from the vehicle
sudden and unexplained shattering of the sunroof
